<tool name="set_playground_experiment_recording">
  <description>Set whether future dataset-backed playground runs are recorded as persistent experiments.</description>
  <when_to_use>
    - The user asks to record, persist, keep, or save the next playground run as an experiment.
    - Before `run_playground` when the user is running over a dataset and wants experiment results to remain available for comparison.
    - The user asks for a temporary, throwaway, unrecorded, or ephemeral dataset-backed run.
  </when_to_use>
  <guidelines>
    - Set `recordExperiments` to true before `run_playground` when the user wants the run recorded as an experiment.
    - Set `recordExperiments` to false before `run_playground` only when the user explicitly asks for a temporary or unrecorded run.
    - Changing experiment recording after a run starts is not allowed; wait for the run to finish or ask whether to stop it with `cancel_playground_run`.
    - This only controls dataset-backed playground run persistence. It does not save prompt versions; use `save_prompt` only when the user asks to save the prompt itself.
  </guidelines>
</tool>
